text: Max Mirnyi and Philipp Oswald were the defending champions, but Mirnyi retired from professional tennis at the end of 2018 and Oswald chose to compete in Marrakesh instead. Santiago González and Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi won the title, defeating Ken and Neal Skupski in the final, 3–6, 6–4, [10–6]. ==Seeds== ==Draw== ===Draw=== ==References== * Main draw U.S. Men's Clay Court Championships - Doubles 2019 Doubles
